article.description: Christian Terrell scored five of his 20 points in overtime and Florida Gulf Coast beat Florida International 84-76 on Sunday.
article.headline: Florida Gulf Coast beats Florida International 84-76 in OT
article.linkText: Florida Gulf Coast beats Florida International 84-76 in OT
article.story: MIAMI -- Christian Terrell scored five of his 20 points in overtime and Florida Gulf Coast beat Florida International 84-76 on Sunday. The Eagles opened overtime on a 10-0 run. Terrell made a 3-pointer and two free throws during the stretch. The Golden Panthers didn't score in the extra period until Adrian Diaz made a dunk with five seconds left. FIU missed five layups and two 3-pointers, and had five turnovers in overtime. Marc Eddy Norelia scored 13 points and grabbed 11 rebounds for Florida Gulf Coast (5-4). Zach Johnson added 12 points with six assists. Diaz had 19 points, nine rebounds, seven blocks and three steals to lead Florida International (4-5). Daviyon Draper made a pair of free throws to give FIU a 71-67 lead with 1:41 left. Terrell answered with a jumper, and Demetris Morant had a dunk to tie it at 71 with seven seconds left to force overtime.
